title: Episode 07: Intro to Behavioural Interviews
author: Jackson Gabbard
description:
Growing up in Nashville and having no access to high technology, I was at a huge disadvantage trying to become a coder. If it hadn't been for luck, my parents buying a PC and letting me do things to it, Robert X Cringely's NerdTV, and lots of hours tinkering, I would never have made it.

So, my first (public) project after leaving Facebook is a YouTube video series trying to offer to people like me the resources I didn't have access to when I was but a fledgling coder trying to make my way in the world.
